The Chronicle In a story of an offending smoking advert we carried yesterday it was stated that the billboard that was advertising a brand of cigarettes near Mpopoma High School belonged to Askeland Media. <img class="size-full wp-image-631795" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/today7-1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/today7-1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/07/today7-1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Mpopoma High School It has since been established that the billboard does not belong to Askeland Media. We therefore want to apologise to Askeland Media for any inconvenience this misrepresentation might have caused. — Editor